<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-798-232  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 798 232.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computerworld  August 27 1990 v24 n35 p96(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Languages: the new generation. (C and C++ programming languages)(Marketplace)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Keyes, Jessica.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Computer programming languages such as assembler and COBOL arestill useful for some purposes but they are giving way to newerlanguages that are more flexible, easier to use and more suited tocontemporary processing methods.andP;  C and C++ are the languagesbeing used as program development tools for many applications,while Lisp and Prolog are popular in artificial intelligenceresearch.andP;  The major advantage of the C programming language isportability; it runs on all kinds of micro-, mini- and mainframecomputers and workstations because of its core language coupledwith libraries developed as needed for an enormous array offunctions.andP;  C may be unique in its ability to manage both theapplication and the operating system internally.andP;  C++ extends C toobject-oriented programming.andP;  Clipper is another of the newerlanguages that score well in portability and the flexibilitygained from using libraries.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Product:   C++ (Program development software) (usage).andO;Topic:     C Programming LanguageHistory of ComputingProgram Development Tools.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>